-- Lehman says replaced COO Gregory to stay with firm
-- 
-- Thu Jun 12, 2008 10:02am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/12/us-lehman-gregory-idUSWEN622220080612

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Joseph Gregory, former president and chief operating officer of Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc, will stay with the firm in an unspecified capacity, a spokesman said on Thursday. 

 Lehman said on Thursday that Bart McDade would replace Gregory as president and COO. (Reporting by  Dan Wilchins , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)